Eco Boardcompany is planning to build a greenfield board production plant in the heart of the port of Amsterdam.
The plant will be producing the innovative Boardeco ecological boards with a production capacity of 240,000 m3 per year. Production is estimated to start in the first quarter of 2020.
The total investment is reported to be 100 million euros and the plant should provide direct employment for close to 80 people.
The plant will be constructed based on the latest sustainability building guidelines and will rely upon certified green energy for its power and heat requirements.
